5. CASE STUDIES

5.1 Smart Manufacturing: Automotive Assembly Line

5.1.1 Challenge

A major automotive manufacturer faced:

· 12% production inefficiency from uncoordinated processes
· 15% unplanned downtime annually
· 3 cybersecurity incidents per month affecting production
· $50M annual losses from quality issues and downtime

5.1.2 Implementation

We deployed a Hybrid Intelligent System across their 3 assembly lines:

Optimization Subsystem:

· Multi-objective optimization of production scheduling
· Real-time adjustment of robot speeds and paths
· Energy consumption minimization while maintaining throughput

Maintenance Subsystem:

· Vibration analysis on 200+ robots for early fault detection
· Thermal imaging for electrical component monitoring
· Predictive maintenance scheduling based on RUL predictions

Security Subsystem:

· Network traffic analysis for anomalous control commands
· Physical access monitoring via computer vision
· Adversarial detection in quality control AI models

Meta-Coordination:

· Dynamic prioritization: quality vs. throughput vs. energy
· Conflict resolution between maintenance and production
· Resource allocation during security incidents

5.1.3 Results

```
Before HIS Implementation:
• Overall Equipment Effectiveness (OEE): 68%
• Mean Time Between Failures (MTBF): 120 hours
• Mean Time To Repair (MTTR): 8 hours
• Security Incident Detection Rate: 65%
• Energy Efficiency: 72%

After 12 Months with HIS:
• OEE: 89% (+21%)
• MTBF: 320 hours (+167%)
• MTTR: 2.5 hours (-69%)
• Security Detection Rate: 96% (+31%)
• Energy Efficiency: 88% (+16%)
• ROI: 4.2x
```

